  "prompt": "How have six species of sloths managed to survive despite their slow movement?",
  "response": "Sloths have survived despite their slow movement through several adaptive strategies:\n\n1. Camouflage\n- Their fur blends in with tree branches and vegetation\n- Reduces visibility to predators\n- Algae growth on their fur helps them blend into forest environments\n\n2. Energy Conservation\n- Extremely low metabolic rate\n- Minimal energy expenditure through slow movement\n- Can survive on limited food resources\n\n3. Arboreal Habitat\n- Spend most time high in trees\n- Reduces exposure to ground predators\n- Provides protection and access to food sources\n\n4. Defensive Mechanisms\n- Sharp claws for defense\n- Ability to remain motionless for long periods\n- Difficult for predators to detect when stationary\n\n5. Digestive Adaptations\n- Complex, multi-chambered stomachs\n- Ability to digest low-nutrient plant materials\n- Can extract maximum nutrients from limited food\n\n6. Limited Predator Presence\n- Live in relatively isolated forest environments\n- Fewer predators in their specific habitats\n- Reduced competition for resources\n\nThese adaptations have allowed sloths to survive and maintain their unique ecological niche despite seemingly disadvantageous physical characteristics like slow movement.",
